 came from a more rural, less professional background. For anyone interested in the roots of jazz and blues, Blues on Stage offers a new and comprehensive introduction to the development of this American musical style.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAfrican American singersxHistoryy20th century. 0aAfrican American women singersxHistoryy20th century. 0aAfrican AmericansxMusicxHistory and criticism. 0aBlues (Music)yTo 1931xHistory and criticism. 0aMusic and racezUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aNineteen twenties. 0aSound recording industryzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 4aAfrican American Studies : African American Studies. 4aAmerican Studies : American Studies. 4aCultural Studies : Popular Culture. 4aFilm, Visual Culture, and Performing Arts : Music. 4aFilm, Visual Culture, and Performing Arts : Performing Arts. 4aGeneral Interest : General Interest. 7aMUSIC / Genres & Styles / Blues.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2023z978311149193640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143849156140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438491561423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438491561/original  a978-3-11-149193-6  SUNY Press eBook Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles